==Korean==
===Verb===
'''있다''' (itta)
#To be (in a place)
#:뉴욕 시는 미국에 '''있다'''. Nyuyok sineun miguge '''itta'''. <br /> New York City '''is''' in the United States. 
#There is/there are
#:물속에 물고기가 '''있어'''요. Mulsoge mulgogiga '''isseo'''yo. <br />'''There''' are fish in the water. 
#To have
#:그녀에게 남자친구가 '''있어'''요. Geunyeoege namjachinguga '''isseo'''yo. <br /> She '''has''' a boyfriend. 
#(auxiliary) indicates a resultant state or location
#:서 '''있다''' ''seo '''itta''''' be standing
#:모여 '''있다''' ''moyeo '''itta''''' be gathered 
#(auxiliary) indicates an action in progress
#:울고 '''있다'''. ''ulgo '''itta'''''.  be crying

==Antonym==
#[[없다]] ''eopda'' (to lack, to be absent).  

